1
00:00:07,299 --> 00:00:08,717
We had...

2
00:00:09,593 --> 00:00:12,095
no other choice but to do this.

3
00:00:12,804 --> 00:00:15,182
No other choice...

4
00:00:16,183 --> 00:00:17,768
but to do this.

5
00:00:22,272 --> 00:00:27,068
THE DAY BEFORE THE YAGIBUSHI FESTIVAL

6
00:00:33,909 --> 00:00:36,827
Think... Think...

7
00:00:36,828 --> 00:00:38,246
Think of something...

8
00:00:38,247 --> 00:00:39,872
THINGS WE COULD DO BY TOMORROW

9
00:00:39,873 --> 00:00:43,584
Think of something
that will make Nakamura laugh again...

10
00:00:43,585 --> 00:00:45,169
TOMORROW! WHAT COULD WE DO?

11
00:00:45,170 --> 00:00:47,129
WHAT'S A TRUE PERVERT?
WHAT WILL MAKE NAKAMURA HAPPY?

12
00:00:56,473 --> 00:00:57,766
Nakamura!

13
00:01:02,187 --> 00:01:03,355
Nanako...

14
00:01:04,106 --> 00:01:05,857
turned herself in to the police.

15
00:01:06,692 --> 00:01:08,067
What?

16
00:01:08,068 --> 00:01:09,570
It's your fault.

17
00:01:10,070 --> 00:01:11,904
Taking her gym clothes,

18
00:01:11,905 --> 00:01:15,284
vandalizing the classroom,
stealing underwear... it was all you!

19
00:01:16,118 --> 00:01:17,785
- No...
- What's that?

20
00:01:17,786 --> 00:01:21,205
I know everything!
About your fort on the riverbank and all!

21
00:01:24,710 --> 00:01:26,502
I'm gonna tell everybody!

22
00:01:26,503 --> 00:01:28,422
You deserve to go to hell!

23
00:01:34,094 --> 00:01:35,387
Well, well.

24
00:01:36,555 --> 00:01:38,472
Hello there, Takao.

25
00:01:38,473 --> 00:01:40,017
Just who we wanted to see.

26
00:01:53,780 --> 00:01:55,407
That fire on the riverbank...

27
00:01:56,491 --> 00:01:58,410
You were there, weren't you?

28
00:02:00,579 --> 00:02:01,580
Yes.

29
00:02:02,706 --> 00:02:05,375
- What about it?
- Why were you there?

30
00:02:06,209 --> 00:02:07,544
Do you know anything?

31
00:02:09,421 --> 00:02:10,422
No.

32
00:02:11,381 --> 00:02:13,967
I happened to see it
on my way back from the bookstore.

33
00:02:16,094 --> 00:02:17,220
Then...

34
00:02:20,849 --> 00:02:22,934
Do you know anything about this notebook?

35
00:02:24,353 --> 00:02:25,646
No, I don't.

36
00:02:27,314 --> 00:02:28,398
I see.

37
00:02:31,068 --> 00:02:32,361
The thing is...

38
00:02:34,780 --> 00:02:38,283
Your name and Sawa Nakamura's name
appear in this notebook.

39
00:02:42,162 --> 00:02:43,705
You say that...

40
00:02:45,040 --> 00:02:47,375
But do you even have proof
that I wrote it?

41
00:02:47,376 --> 00:02:49,960
- Come on, Takao.
- I said I don't know anything!

42
00:02:49,961 --> 00:02:51,463
What's with you?

43
00:02:56,551 --> 00:02:57,844
Sorry about that.

44
00:02:58,428 --> 00:03:01,056
If you remember anything,
let us know anytime.

45
00:03:11,858 --> 00:03:14,111
All right, thank you. We'll be going now.

46
00:04:48,663 --> 00:04:50,998
THE FLOWERS OF EVIL

47
00:04:50,999 --> 00:04:53,292
Apparently, it was all Nakamura's plan.

48
00:04:53,293 --> 00:04:55,002
Right, that makes sense.

49
00:04:55,003 --> 00:04:56,086
EPISODE 7

50
00:04:56,087 --> 00:04:58,839
Kasuga was working
under Nakamura's direction.

51
00:04:58,840 --> 00:05:00,800
- It's only a rumor, though.
- Sure.

52
00:05:00,801 --> 00:05:03,260
I wonder if she has something on him?

53
00:05:03,261 --> 00:05:05,262
So, Nakamura was behind those thefts?

54
00:05:05,263 --> 00:05:07,932
And, she even forced him
to put the gym clothes on.

55
00:05:07,933 --> 00:05:09,266
- No, seriously?
- Really?

56
00:05:09,267 --> 00:05:10,810
Nakamura's got a weird fetish!

57
00:05:10,811 --> 00:05:13,020
Some people say Nakamura was the arsonist.

58
00:05:13,021 --> 00:05:14,522
Yeah, Nanako wouldn't do that.

59
00:05:14,523 --> 00:05:17,024
- I know, right? She's deranged!
- I can't even.

60
00:05:17,025 --> 00:05:20,152
-  Yeah, it's disgusting.
-  Why would she do that?

61
00:05:20,153 --> 00:05:22,697
-  I can't even imagine why.
-  She gives me the creeps!

62
00:05:27,619 --> 00:05:29,119
PRINCIPAL'S OFFICE

63
00:05:29,120 --> 00:05:30,997
Let me get straight
to the point.

64
00:05:31,581 --> 00:05:32,833
The gym clothes,

65
00:05:33,416 --> 00:05:34,668
the classroom,

66
00:05:35,293 --> 00:05:37,671
and, well... the girls' underwear...

67
00:05:38,171 --> 00:05:39,840
Did you do all of that?

68
00:05:41,925 --> 00:05:43,802
Why would you do something like that?

69
00:05:45,387 --> 00:05:46,721
Why?

70
00:05:49,182 --> 00:05:50,267
That's...

71
00:05:51,768 --> 00:05:53,562
I can't articulate why.

72
00:05:54,354 --> 00:05:55,355
Takao,

73
00:05:55,856 --> 00:05:58,817
you need to explain yourself
and exactly what you did.

74
00:06:01,069 --> 00:06:02,237
Shit bug.

75
00:06:03,280 --> 00:06:04,573
What?

76
00:06:07,742 --> 00:06:09,119
This town,

77
00:06:09,703 --> 00:06:10,704
myself,

78
00:06:11,580 --> 00:06:13,622
we're all shit bugs. That's why.

79
00:06:13,623 --> 00:06:15,458
'Cause we're all empty pieces of shit.

80
00:06:16,459 --> 00:06:17,627
Still,

81
00:06:18,253 --> 00:06:19,921
I wanted to do something about it.

82
00:06:21,131 --> 00:06:24,134
I wanted to find something precious
I could call my own.

83
00:06:25,969 --> 00:06:28,430
So, I had no other choice but to do this.

84
00:06:31,641 --> 00:06:34,269
Well, he's only a child, after all.

85
00:06:35,520 --> 00:06:36,938
It was Nakamura, wasn't it?

86
00:06:39,399 --> 00:06:41,776
Nakamura made you do it, didn't she?

87
00:06:43,820 --> 00:06:44,821
What?

88
00:06:47,782 --> 00:06:50,618
Why do you jump to conclusions like that?

89
00:06:50,619 --> 00:06:52,202
That's what Nakamura can't stand!

90
00:06:52,203 --> 00:06:53,454
Why don't you get it?

91
00:06:53,455 --> 00:06:55,081
Takao! I'm sorry, sir.

92
00:06:56,958 --> 00:06:57,959
Come in.

93
00:06:59,169 --> 00:07:00,170
It's Nakamura.

94
00:07:01,296 --> 00:07:02,797
Why don't we ask her directly?

95
00:07:08,553 --> 00:07:09,929
I'm sorry.

96
00:07:10,889 --> 00:07:13,098
She resisted and got out of control...

97
00:07:13,099 --> 00:07:14,809
I couldn't get Sawa to come.

98
00:07:16,770 --> 00:07:19,189
I knew she'd cause trouble someday.

99
00:07:20,565 --> 00:07:22,317
She's very difficult...

100
00:07:24,361 --> 00:07:26,029
Just like her mother.

101
00:07:39,292 --> 00:07:40,418
Takao,

102
00:07:40,919 --> 00:07:43,420
we're going to move
during this summer break.

103
00:07:43,421 --> 00:07:44,422
What?

104
00:07:45,340 --> 00:07:46,423
Why?

105
00:07:46,424 --> 00:07:47,675
In a town like this,

106
00:07:47,676 --> 00:07:49,260
rumors go around fast.

107
00:07:50,136 --> 00:07:51,930
The Nakamuras are moving, too.

108
00:07:55,225 --> 00:07:57,811
We can't live in this town anymore.

109
00:08:03,233 --> 00:08:04,401
I don't want to move.

110
00:08:06,027 --> 00:08:08,946
I still have something
I have to do in this town.

111
00:08:08,947 --> 00:08:10,573
It's already been decided.

112
00:08:11,074 --> 00:08:13,201
That'll be what's best for you, too.

113
00:08:15,745 --> 00:08:16,871
Why...

114
00:08:18,373 --> 00:08:20,874
Why do you only care
about what people think?

115
00:08:20,875 --> 00:08:23,377
You're the one who made me read
The Flowers of Evil.

116
00:08:23,378 --> 00:08:26,381
You taught me about the real things
dumb people don't understand!

117
00:08:28,007 --> 00:08:29,259
Hey, Dad.

118
00:08:29,759 --> 00:08:31,761
Why did you marry mom?

119
00:08:32,262 --> 00:08:33,721
Did you settle for her?

120
00:08:33,722 --> 00:08:35,597
Then you're the shit bug, Dad!

121
00:08:35,598 --> 00:08:37,307
That is enough!

122
00:08:37,308 --> 00:08:39,978
Imagine how we're feeling for a change!

123
00:08:40,812 --> 00:08:42,396
What in the world...

124
00:08:42,397 --> 00:08:44,441
What are you trying to do?!

125
00:08:46,276 --> 00:08:48,945
Help me, please...

126
00:08:53,908 --> 00:08:56,327
Think about what you've done.

127
00:08:57,245 --> 00:08:59,080
You're grounded as of today.

128
00:09:18,933 --> 00:09:23,604
DIE - A CRIMINAL LIVES HERE
PERVERTED BITCH - ARSONIST

129
00:09:23,605 --> 00:09:27,901
GET OUT, MONSTER
CURSE YOU

130
00:09:40,246 --> 00:09:41,623
What did I...

131
00:09:42,207 --> 00:09:44,709
What did I do all that for?

132
00:09:45,919 --> 00:09:47,253
Saeki...

133
00:09:47,962 --> 00:09:49,963
Nakamura...

134
00:09:49,964 --> 00:09:51,257
Myself...

135
00:09:52,217 --> 00:09:53,968
I couldn't give life to any of us.

136
00:09:56,221 --> 00:09:57,388
I...

137
00:09:58,181 --> 00:10:00,225
couldn't live in this town.

138
00:10:03,269 --> 00:10:04,312
What...

139
00:10:05,855 --> 00:10:07,689
should I have done?

140
00:10:13,321 --> 00:10:14,656
Nakamura...

141
00:10:15,990 --> 00:10:17,200
Nakamura!

142
00:11:04,247 --> 00:11:05,999
Hey, you two stop right there!

143
00:11:11,921 --> 00:11:14,715
Are you all right?

144
00:11:14,716 --> 00:11:16,842
Nakamura...

145
00:11:16,843 --> 00:11:18,052
Nakamura!

146
00:11:39,032 --> 00:11:40,158
Get off.

147
00:12:26,996 --> 00:12:29,290
Take your clothes off, Kasuga.

148
00:12:30,333 --> 00:12:31,376
What?

149
00:12:32,210 --> 00:12:33,419
Why?

150
00:12:37,632 --> 00:12:38,883
Hurry up.

151
00:13:16,838 --> 00:13:18,631
Everything.

152
00:13:19,257 --> 00:13:20,632
What?

153
00:13:41,696 --> 00:13:44,532
You're still hiding your true self.

154
00:13:48,870 --> 00:13:52,457
I said I'd peel back all your layers, remember?

155
00:13:54,959 --> 00:13:56,209
Stand up straight.

156
00:14:00,089 --> 00:14:01,758
Take off all your layers.

157
00:14:04,218 --> 00:14:06,095
We're running out of time.

158
00:14:08,347 --> 00:14:10,557
Come on, Kasuga!

159
00:14:13,561 --> 00:14:16,188
I told you to stand straight.

160
00:14:19,567 --> 00:14:20,651
Sorry...

161
00:14:21,319 --> 00:14:22,445
I'm sorry...

162
00:14:23,780 --> 00:14:25,656
Why are you apologizing?

163
00:14:27,450 --> 00:14:28,826
Nakamura,

164
00:14:30,620 --> 00:14:32,287
the other side is...

165
00:14:32,288 --> 00:14:34,373
It's inside of you.

166
00:14:35,583 --> 00:14:37,126
I want to save you.

167
00:14:38,044 --> 00:14:39,961
I'll do anything to save you!

168
00:14:44,217 --> 00:14:45,593
Don't be ridiculous!

169
00:14:53,601 --> 00:14:54,977
It was always...

170
00:14:55,937 --> 00:14:57,438
Always...

171
00:14:58,022 --> 00:15:00,608
Screaming.

172
00:15:02,527 --> 00:15:04,111
Inside me...

173
00:15:04,112 --> 00:15:06,989
The perverted thing down there...

174
00:15:07,949 --> 00:15:12,744
It had been screaming
in words I couldn't understand.

175
00:15:18,042 --> 00:15:19,669
That voice...

176
00:15:21,712 --> 00:15:24,632
echoed back from you, Kasuga.

177
00:15:25,842 --> 00:15:28,010
And I could finally hear it.

178
00:15:31,764 --> 00:15:33,558
"Get me out of here."

179
00:15:34,725 --> 00:15:36,602
"How can I get out?"

180
00:15:37,311 --> 00:15:39,438
"Where's the other side?"

181
00:15:42,525 --> 00:15:44,861
But, I finally realized.

182
00:15:48,322 --> 00:15:50,533
There is no "other side."

183
00:15:51,993 --> 00:15:57,081
There's no "this side," either.
No shit bugs, no perverts.

184
00:15:59,584 --> 00:16:00,959
There's...

185
00:16:00,960 --> 00:16:02,795
nothing left...

186
00:16:07,425 --> 00:16:09,218
Because, no matter where I go,

187
00:16:10,011 --> 00:16:13,639
I can't get away from myself.

188
00:16:25,735 --> 00:16:27,862
This is my last order to you.

189
00:16:29,655 --> 00:16:31,199
Use this bat

190
00:16:31,782 --> 00:16:34,452
and smash my brains out.

191
00:16:36,120 --> 00:16:39,415
Beat them into mush,
so there's nothing left.

192
00:16:42,501 --> 00:16:44,879
That'll be the end of our contract.

193
00:17:19,080 --> 00:17:20,790
Tomorrow...

194
00:17:21,457 --> 00:17:23,167
Why don't we throw it all away?

195
00:17:25,002 --> 00:17:27,129
Let's throw away our lives from here on...

196
00:17:28,673 --> 00:17:29,799
All of it.

197
00:17:42,019 --> 00:17:43,688
Are you coming with me?

198
00:17:51,362 --> 00:17:52,363
Yeah.

199
00:17:59,453 --> 00:18:01,122
What was she like at home?

200
00:18:01,706 --> 00:18:03,332
What was Nanako like, usually?

201
00:18:03,958 --> 00:18:04,959
Right.

202
00:18:06,335 --> 00:18:08,462
Nanako is a very good girl.

203
00:18:10,214 --> 00:18:12,883
She's always dedicated herself
to anything she did.

204
00:18:13,384 --> 00:18:15,511
She'd tell me everything.

205
00:18:17,555 --> 00:18:19,181
Do you really think so, though?

206
00:18:19,765 --> 00:18:23,185
Perhaps you were only playing
the model student mom wanted you to be.

207
00:18:24,228 --> 00:18:26,230
You were holding yourself in, right?

208
00:18:30,818 --> 00:18:31,902
No, I wasn't.

209
00:18:36,907 --> 00:18:39,160
That boy, Kasuga...

210
00:18:40,286 --> 00:18:41,329
You know...

211
00:18:42,079 --> 00:18:43,289
I met him.

212
00:18:45,374 --> 00:18:47,835
What does he mean to you?

213
00:18:49,629 --> 00:18:50,880
Nothing, really...

214
00:18:52,089 --> 00:18:54,050
He's just a classmate.

215
00:18:55,926 --> 00:18:57,470
Nothing noteworthy...

216
00:18:58,554 --> 00:19:00,348
a plain, straight-laced...

217
00:19:05,519 --> 00:19:06,854
It's beautiful.

218
00:19:12,568 --> 00:19:15,655
So slimy and messy...

219
00:19:16,197 --> 00:19:20,117
Like shit-filled sewer waste.
It's beautiful.

220
00:19:23,954 --> 00:19:25,289
You're right. It is.

221
00:19:26,457 --> 00:19:29,001
GAUZE MASKS

222
00:19:34,507 --> 00:19:36,174
My sincerest apologies!

223
00:19:36,175 --> 00:19:38,009
My daughter did the unthinkable!

224
00:19:38,010 --> 00:19:40,428
Please stop.
It's really not that big of a deal.

225
00:19:40,429 --> 00:19:41,722
I'm...

226
00:19:42,682 --> 00:19:44,600
I'm a failure of a mother.

227
00:19:45,184 --> 00:19:47,395
It's my fault that Takao is...

228
00:19:52,108 --> 00:19:54,819
We need to find those two
or who knows what they'll do...

229
00:19:55,403 --> 00:20:01,324
THE ANNUAL HIKARI CITY YAGIBUSHI FESTIVAL
LIVE BROADCASTING

230
00:20:01,325 --> 00:20:03,034
Hello, ladies and gentlemen!

231
00:20:03,035 --> 00:20:06,871
We're coming to you live from
the Yagibushi Festival once again!

232
00:20:08,541 --> 00:20:12,669
There are so many people here already,
and the place is filled with excitement.

233
00:20:38,654 --> 00:20:39,989
The summer festival?

234
00:20:40,573 --> 00:20:41,574
What?

235
00:20:43,075 --> 00:20:45,994
It was marked in the calendar
in Sawa's room.

236
00:20:45,995 --> 00:20:47,078
FESTIVAL

237
00:20:47,079 --> 00:20:49,415
She's never cared
about the festival before...

238
00:20:55,963 --> 00:20:57,256
Ma'am!

239
00:21:06,974 --> 00:21:09,935
HIKARI YAGIBUSHI

240
00:21:21,238 --> 00:21:24,909
KEROSENE

241
00:21:37,671 --> 00:21:39,714
No way! That should've gone down!

242
00:21:39,715 --> 00:21:42,008
- That's not right.
-  It's karma.

243
00:21:42,009 --> 00:21:43,219
-  Yamada...
-  Huh?

244
00:21:44,094 --> 00:21:45,470
Have you seen Kasuga?

245
00:21:45,471 --> 00:21:47,430
What? He's here?

246
00:21:47,431 --> 00:21:48,432
No clue.

247
00:21:59,318 --> 00:22:01,695
Excuse me! Sorry!

248
00:22:02,446 --> 00:22:04,114
Run, get away! Hurry!

249
00:22:07,284 --> 00:22:12,039
-  It's not safe! Please get back!
-  Get away from the bandstand!

250
00:22:15,376 --> 00:22:16,709
We have an emergency!

251
00:22:16,710 --> 00:22:20,421
Suspicious individuals with knives
are on the festival platform!

252
00:22:20,422 --> 00:22:24,050
It appears nobody has been injured.
I repeat!

253
00:22:24,051 --> 00:22:27,387
Suspicious individuals with knives
are on the festival platform!

254
00:22:27,388 --> 00:22:29,807
People are panic-stricken!

255
00:22:30,891 --> 00:22:33,601
The two have taken their masks off!

256
00:22:33,602 --> 00:22:35,688
It's a boy and a girl!

257
00:22:40,442 --> 00:22:42,068
To the shit bugs!

258
00:22:42,069 --> 00:22:45,114
To all the shit bugs of this town!

259
00:22:48,492 --> 00:22:50,869
TO BE CONTINUED

260
00:23:47,927 --> 00:23:49,010
ON THE NEXT EPISODE

261
00:23:49,011 --> 00:23:51,721
Kasuga and Nakamura
take their biggest stage

262
00:23:51,722 --> 00:23:54,974
as shit bugs surround them.

263
00:23:54,975 --> 00:23:56,602
Next, on episode eight,

264
00:23:57,436 --> 00:24:00,813
will the young two be able
to reach the other side?

265
00:24:00,814 --> 00:24:02,858
Translated by Yuka Kristi
